President Obama has announced his intention to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Kenny Alameda will be the United States Commissioner for the Commission for the Conservation and Management of Highly Migratory Fish Stocks in the Western and Central Pacific Ocean. Joye Frost will be the Director of the Office for Victims of Crime at the Department of Justice. Marlene Sallo will be the Staff Director for the United States Commission on Civil Rights. Robert Wolf will be a member of the President's Export Council. Steve Bennett will be a member of the President's National Security Telecommunications Advisory Committee. Angel Ruiz will also be a member of the President's National Security Telecommunications Advisory Committee. President Obama expressed gratitude to these individuals for their willingness to serve the American people.